text: Ixora temehaniensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae. It is endemic to the island Raiatea in French Polynesia. ==Sources== * Florence, J. 1998. Ixora temehaniensis. 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.
